title: Green Breeze Imports RFID Shielded Natural Abaca Fiber Large Wallet
features: Natural Fiber Abaca ( aka Manila Hemp) sport wallet. RFID shielded liner surrounds entire contents.
6 Colors for Every Taste. Color range from coservative to bold. Red people know who they are.
Internal lining provides 99.9999% shielding in the range 10 to 3000 Mhz according to fabric manufacturer tests.
Handmade Wallet of Hand-Dyed Abaca Jute Fiber. Also called Manila Hemp. Abaca is the strongest natural fiber for exceptional wear.
description: A plant-fiber tri-fold wallet made of natural hand-dyed abaca. This roomy wallet has 7 compartments to organize your things yet still be slim enough for the back pocket. Velcro closure allows you to store plenty in this wallet. Abaca is a natural plant fiber made from banana leaves. Abaca is the strongest natural fiber, on par with nylon for strength and is highly resistant to salt water damage. While a leather wallet will soak up sweat and plastic wallet will become yucky, this will remain undamaged and can be washed. Compartments include an open pouch for money, and secure zipper pouch for bills or papers, a front easy-access pouch for credit cards, two hidden credit card pouches for seldom used cards or coupons, a clear plastic pouch for pictures of loved ones, and a zipper coin pouch for coins or keys. Wallet is 9.75 inches by 5 inches unfolded and 3.5 inches by 5 inches when folded. This wallet is slightly over-sized, so that it becomes the more usual size when you have it full. This wallet has a RFID-shielding conductive-lining. For the techie: The lining material provides 99.9999% shielding in the range 10 to 3000 MHz.
